The move command, m, lets you rearrange blocks of audio data.  It needs a
block address, or a comma separated pair of them, in front of the command
to tell which blocks to move, and a single block address after it, to
tell where to move it.  No spaces may appear from beginning to end of
this command.  Omitting the addresses in front means to move the current
block, and omitting the address following the m means to move the data
to the current block.  The data to be moved are placed following the
destination, unless the destination is block one, in which case they
are moved ahead of it.

